UNDIAGNOSED ILLNESS, BAT GUANO RELATED - USA (TEXAS): REQUEST FOR INFO
**********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Tue, 28 Jul 1998 17:20:03 -600
From: James L. Alexander, DVM, MPVM <DrJames.Alexander@tdh.state.tx.us>

I am not sure this is appropriate for ProMED-mail but since there is such a
broad range of professional expertise available I thought it worth submitting.
I have responded to this individual that cryptococcosis and histoplasmosis
are two possibilities. Crypto is described as having CNS symptoms, but
histo isn't. I have posed some questions to him regarding being
immunocompromised. I have not yet heard back from him.
I also told him rabies is not a probable cause, hoping that this isn't a
case of a very long incubation period for rabies superimposed over histo.
One case of human rabies occurred in a spelunker about 3 years after his
last entry to a cave. I recommended that he have his physician contact CDC
immediately if rabies is suspected.
--
Jim Alexander, DVM, MPVM, ACVPM
Director, West Texas Rabies Response Center
Texas Department of Health
1702 West Avenue N
San Angelo, TX 76904
